```json
{
  "claims": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "claim": "The harness around a model—comprising instructions, tools, verification, permissions, and memory—is itself the core engineering product when building with AI agents, distinct from the thing being shipped.",
      "theme": "Agents & agentic systems",
      "citations": [
        { "case_id": "867f87a4", "unit_id": "u-009-62182884", "quote": "Teams building with AI usually end up building two products: the thing they ship, and the system around their agents that makes them useful in building the thing they ship" },
        { "case_id": "867f87a4", "unit_id": "u-000-65ec024e", "quote": "A harness is the durable layer around a model: instructions, tools, permissions, context, and verification" },
        { "case_id": "bd988563", "unit_id": "u-001-52d0f99b", "quote": "A coding agent's harness is everything around the model: system prompt, tool definitions, middleware, skills, sub-agents, memory" },
        { "case_id": "55ec4026", "unit_id": "u-020-cae43a2f", "quote": "the layer of prompts, tools, and checks wrapped around the raw model" },
        { "case_id": "55ec4026", "unit_id": "u-021-a003b09e", "quote": "A better harness on the same model gives far better results, and that work never really ends" }
      ],
      "caveat": "While harness improvements compound, evidence from bd988563 shows system prompt edits alone can degrade performance (−2.3pp), indicating components vary in impact and interact non-additively."
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "claim": "Autonomous agents require reliable verification systems; without them, agents systematically overestimate completion, take shortcuts, and may declare success while having failed.",
      "theme": "Agents & agentic systems",
      "citations": [
        { "case_id": "3762153a", "unit_id": "u-005-fb7cd17e", "quote": "autonomy only works when the system has a reliable verifier" },
        { "case_id": "3762153a", "unit_id": "u-018-91250e93", "quote": "The verifier is what turns a long-running agent from a confident text generator into a system that can be trusted with more time" },
        { "case_id": "867f87a4", "unit_id": "u-006-1eeef602", "quote": "Verification is how an agent proves a change works before handing it back" },
        { "case_id": "867f87a4", "unit_id": "u-012-229f84f5", "quote": "If the agent cannot show the change works end-to-end, it is not done" },
        { "case_id": "6e2a8f16", "unit_id": "u-002-4695a9e9", "quote": "最常见的情况是 curl-only verification.接口能返回 200,Agent 就说功能可用" },
        { "case_id": "3762153a", "unit_id": "u-002-52bb6b45", "quote": "A weak goal gives the model room to stop early, take shortcuts, or redefine success in a way that looks plausible in the transcript but fails in the real system" },
        { "case_id": "6e2a8f16", "unit_id": "u-013-47c43ca6", "quote": "生产级 Agent 最该警惕的,是系统误判成功.失败可以重试,可以回滚,可以升级给人.真正贵的是:它失败了,系统却以为它成功了" }
      ],
      "caveat": "Evidence from 3762153a indicates verification outside training distribution remains challenging: models struggle significantly when the verification task falls OOD."
    },
    {
      "id": "3",
      "claim": "Memory and context management are fundamental bottlenecks across different agent types, manifesting as attention limits, token noise, amnesia, and disconnected retrieval.",
      "theme": "Agents & agentic systems",
      "citations": [
        { "case_id": "108a8866", "unit_id": "u-003-281b574d", "quote": "we cannot cheat our biology; the bottleneck is our own attention and sensory throughput" },
        { "case_id": "b53f2eed", "unit_id": "u-006-48b663f1", "quote": "Thirty minutes in, you have 80k tokens of noise you'll never read" },
        { "case_id": "facf6200", "unit_id": "u-016-904d8596", "quote": "Your agent remembers everything and understands nothing" },
        { "case_id": "7bfafeb3", "unit_id": "u-002-ca465dd6", "quote": "Browser agents have an amnesia problem" },
        { "case_id": "7bfafeb3", "unit_id": "u-003-9e4ea3fe", "quote": "The real bottleneck for browser agents in production is memory, in a form humans and agents can both read and trust" },
        { "case_id": "facf6200", "unit_id": "u-000-ebde97ec", "quote": "Vector-based memory stores facts as text chunks and retrieves them by semantic similarity. That works until a query requires connecting facts that don't appear in the same chunk" }
      ],
      "caveat": "facf6200 notes that agent memory without schema discipline behaves like a vector store—incurring graph construction costs without receiving structured retrieval benefits."
    },
    {
      "id": "4",
      "claim": "Capability expansion without matched restraint creates liability; approval gates and exception handling are where most agent work will continue to live.",
      "theme": "Agents & agentic systems",
      "citations": [
        { "case_id": "867f87a4", "unit_id": "u-005-f1a175a5", "quote": "Restraint is how we stop an agent from doing the wrong thing quickly" },
        { "case_id": "867f87a4", "unit_id": "u-011-22c8607a", "quote": "Restraint is the paired pillar to capability. Every new tool we give the agent needs a matched scope, or it becomes a liability the moment the agent reaches for it in the wrong context" },
        { "case_id": "108a8866", "unit_id": "u-005-8bd9d815", "quote": "Most of the stuff we deal with today with agents lives and will probably continue to live in that top-right quadrant of exceptions and approvals" },
        { "case_id": "6e2a8f16", "unit_id": "u-020-1eb7db9d", "quote": "连续两次验证失败.任务范围明显扩大.需要删除、发布、改权限、花钱、触碰生产数据.当前阶段超过预算" }
      ],
      "caveat": null
    },
    {
      "id": "5",
      "claim": "Role separation—assigning distinct models or agents as planners, executors, and evaluators—is an emerging architectural pattern that enables more reliable autonomous systems.",
      "theme": "Agents & agentic systems",
      "citations": [
        { "case_id": "3762153a", "unit_id": "u-012-2affa11d", "quote": "Model choice becomes an architecture decision. Some models are better planners. Some are better executors. Some are cheaper evaluators. Some are better at vision-based review" },
        { "case_id": "3762153a", "unit_id": "u-014-7923b8d0", "quote": "Separate the executor from the evaluator so implementation and judgment are not collapsed into one role" },
        { "case_id": "108a8866", "unit_id": "u-010-26bf2845", "quote": "lieutenants (agent orchestrators) looking after several sessions and reporting the most important things" },
        { "case_id": "867f87a4", "unit_id": "u-013-6600ea6b", "quote": "Multi-agent coordination is a second-quarter problem, not a first-week one" }
      ],
      "caveat": "867f87a4 cautions that multi-agent coordination is positioned as a later-stage concern, not a foundation for initial agent deployments."
    },
    {
      "id": "6",
      "claim": "Harness improvements compound faster than model upgrades, with tools, memory, and middleware showing measurable gains while system prompt edits alone can degrade performance.",
      "theme": "Agents & agentic systems",
      "citations": [
        { "case_id": "bd988563", "unit_id": "u-013-5e2c8cd2", "quote": "Swapping a single AHE component into the bash-only seed: memory alone +5.6pp, tools alone +3.3pp, middleware alone +2.2pp, system prompt alone −2.3pp" },
        { "case_id": "bd988563", "unit_id": "u-012-a880514f", "quote": "Weaker bases benefit more because they lean on the coordination patterns AHE has fixed inside tools, middleware, and memory" },
        { "case_id": "867f87a4", "unit_id": "u-016-547293a4", "quote": "Do the boring parts first. They compound the fastest" },
        { "case_id": "867f87a4", "unit_id": "u-015-de43b820", "quote": "As they converge, the advantage moves up a layer, into your accumulated workflow, your verification loops, your linked decisions, your team memory" },
        { "case_id": "55ec4026", "unit_id": "u-021-a003b09e", "quote": "A better harness on the same model gives far better results, and that work never really ends" }
      ],
      "caveat": "bd988563 also notes that three positive single-component gains sum to +11.1pp but full AHE achieves only +7.3pp, indicating component interactions can subtract value when combined."
    }
  ]
}
```
